   <mods:abstract>All disputes over the eastern boundary should be settled as soon as
            possible. Adams should be sent all the papers and instructed to press for a commission
            to settle the line. Each party shall name half. They shall take an oath of impartiality.
            The majority of the whole shall be a quorum. Both parties shall have access to public
            records of the other. A report to be made in three months. All transfers of territory
            shall be made within six months of the decision concerning them.</mods:abstract>
